	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories  At least two train carriages were destroyed by a fire that blazed through a train at the Retreat Railway Station this morning. According to the City of Cape Town’s Fire Department spokesperson, Theo Layne, two passenger coaches were engulfed in flames, while another suffered light fire damage. “Luckily nobody was hurt during this whole episode,” he says. Layne says it is possible that the train was set alight deliberately.   24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  